Rating: 2
I followed the suggestions of the other cooks and found that the broth was too strongly flavored with wine and leeks. I would probably try using just one leek and using closer to a 50-50 mixture of water and wine. I also added a whole pint of cream hoping to minimize the overpowering wine flavor. Overall, it was OK but isn't something I'm eager to make again.

Rating: 4
This was just wonderful! I made it for guests yesterday and they (as well as their young children) just raved about it, saying it was restaurant quality. I omitted the peppers as no one in my family likes them and steamed the mussels in mostly wine with a small bit of water rather than 50% of each. Also added a bit of sherry at the end, as suggested by another reviewer. The flavors were incredible and the soup beautiful to look at. A definite keeper (though next time I will double the liquid -- I make steamed mussels a lot and freeze the liquid, so there's always mussel broth on hand).

