Very tasty chowder, a nice change from the usual white-wine-and-garlic mussel treatment. 8 first-course servings must be teacup-sized as this made a meal with some leftover for 2 adults with average appetites. One red and one yellow pepper made a brighter presentation than all orange.

Rating: 4
This was a very flavorful, yummy dish. Different from New England clam chowder -- this soup was not thick or creamy. We served it with crusty french bread and dry white wine and it was one of the best soups I've ever had. I got mussels precleaned in the store, so making it was quick and easy.

